column13: body=Oh I’m shaking. You talk big but all I see is someone desperate to look tough.
body=We don’t bow to tyrants hiding behind darkness. If it’s a clash of convictions you want
column14: the Legion stands ready. We won’t let your corruption swallow the realm.

column13: body=You cling to that naive radiance like it protects you. The Obsidian Order’s rise is inevitable. Oppose us
column14: and you’ll be swept aside with the rest of the deluded.

column13: body=Your shadows are nothing but fear masquerading as strength. The Legion will burn away every twisted doctrine your Order spreads.
body=Your so-called Dawn Legion is a stain on this realm. Our Order will reshape the world in shadow
column14: whether your light survives or not.

column13: body=Say whatever you want. You’re about to learn that I don’t back down.
body=Good. I’d hate for you to run when things get messy. Let’s see if you can handle what you started.
body=You’ve pushed me for the last time. Keep it up and you’re going to find out exactly why nobody crosses me twice.
body=I'll see if there's donuts in the break room.
body=I accept praise in the form of pastries.
body=Oh wow. Did it finally work?
